<div class="mg-card">
  <div class="mg-card-header">
    <strong>No MySQL connection found</strong>
  </div>
  <div class="mg-card-body">
    <p>
      MysqlGenius could not find a MySQL connection in your Rails application's
      <code>config/database.yml</code> for the
      <strong><%= @rails_env %></strong> environment.
    </p>

    <p>
      Add an entry with one of the MySQL adapters
      (<code>mysql2</code>, <code>trilogy</code>, or <code>jdbcmysql</code>)
      and restart your server. Example:
    </p>

    <pre style="background:#f8f9fa;border:1px solid #dee2e6;border-radius:4px;padding:12px;font-size:12px;overflow:auto;"><code><%= @rails_env %>:
  adapter: mysql2
  encoding: utf8mb4
  database: my_app_<%= @rails_env %>
  username: root
  password: <%%= ENV["MYSQL_PASSWORD"] %>
  host: 127.0.0.1
  port: 3306
  pool: &lt;%%= ENV.fetch("RAILS_MAX_THREADS") { 5 } %&gt;</code></pre>

    <p>
      Have multiple databases? Define each one in <code>database.yml</code>
      — MysqlGenius automatically discovers every MySQL connection Rails
      knows about and shows them as tabs in the dashboard. Writers paired
      with <code>&lt;name&gt;_replica</code> readers will automatically read
      from the replica.
    </p>

    <p style="font-size:12px;color:#666;margin-top:16px;">
      Example of a multi-database configuration:
    </p>
    <pre style="background:#f8f9fa;border:1px solid #dee2e6;border-radius:4px;padding:12px;font-size:12px;overflow:auto;"><code><%= @rails_env %>:
  primary:
    adapter: mysql2
    database: my_app_<%= @rails_env %>
    &lt;&lt;: *default
  primary_replica:
    adapter: mysql2
    database: my_app_<%= @rails_env %>
    replica: true
    &lt;&lt;: *default
  analytics:
    adapter: mysql2
    database: my_app_analytics_<%= @rails_env %>
    &lt;&lt;: *default</code></pre>

    <p style="margin-top:16px;">
      See the
      <a href="https://github.com/antarr/mysql_genius#readme" target="_blank">
        README
      </a>
      for full configuration options.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
